SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp.Description1Txt: YOUNG SCHOLARS PROGRAM - SUPPORTS A GROWING NETWORK OF EARLY CAREER SCHOLARS TAKING ON RESEARCH PROJECTS THAT ARE POLICY- AND PRACTICE-RELEVANT AND, AT THIS TIME, EXAMINE THE PREPARATION, COMPENSATION, WELL-BEING, AND ON-GOING PROFESSIONAL LEARNING OF THE EARLY CARE AND EDUCATION WORKFORCE. THE FOUNDATION AWARDS GRANTS TO SUPPORT THEIR WORK, CONVENES MEETINGS AND WORKSHOPS THAT ENCOURAGE NETWORKING AND MENTORING, AND PROVIDES PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT TO BUILD RESEARCH AND COMMUNICATIONS SKILLS. THIS PROGRAM HAS PROVIDED SUPPORT TO 70 YOUNG SCHOLARS AND 15 PROMISING SCHOLARS.
SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp.Description2Txt: POLICY & COMMUNICATIONS PROGRAM - LEVERAGES AND AUGMENTS THE IMPACT OF THE FOUNDATION'S GRANTS THROUGH A STRATEGIC COMMUNICATIONS PROGRAM THAT REACHES OUT TO THE FIELD OF EARLY EDUCATION RESEARCHERS, PRACTITIONERS, POLICY MAKERS, AND THE GENERAL PUBLIC THROUGH PUBLICATIONS, AN ELECTRONIC NEWSLETTER, SOCIAL MEDIA, AND CONVENINGS.

ApplicationSubmissionInfoGrp.FormAndInfoAndMaterialsTxt: THE FOUNDATION FOR CHILD DEVELOPMENT DOES NOT ACCEPT UNSOLICITED PROPOSALS, RATHER, REQUESTS FOR FUNDING ARE SUBMITTED TO THE FOUNDATION BY INVITATION ONLY. WE FUND ORGANIZATIONS THAT ARE NON-PROFIT, PUBLIC CHARITIES AS RECOGNIZED BY THE UNITED STATES INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE UNDER THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE 501(C)(3). OUR YOUNG SCHOLARS PROGRAM FOR FELLOWSHIP GRANTS IS OUR ONLY OPEN COMPETITION. PLEASE VISIT THE YOUNG SCHOLARS PROGRAM PAGE FOR MORE INFORMATION ABOUT ELIGIBILITY AND THE APPLICATION PROCESS.
